  "prompt": "The future of elementary school libraries?",
  "response": "The future of elementary school libraries is likely to involve:\n\n1. Technology Integration\n- Digital resources and e-books\n- Interactive learning platforms\n- Maker spaces with coding and tech stations\n- Digital literacy skills development\n\n2. Flexible Learning Spaces\n- Collaborative work areas\n- Movable furniture\n- Multi-purpose design\n- Comfortable reading zones\n\n3. Expanded Learning Roles\n- Research and information literacy centers\n- STEM/STEAM programming\n- Social-emotional learning support\n- Multimedia creation spaces\n\n4. Diverse Resource Collections\n- Multicultural and inclusive book selections\n- Multimedia resources\n- Print and digital materials\n- Accessible content for different learning styles\n\n5. Community Engagement\n- Family literacy programs\n- After-school activities\n- Partnerships with local organizations\n- Technology workshops\n\n6. Personalized Learning\n- Adaptive digital resources\n- Individual learning paths\n- Recommendation systems\n- Student-centered design\n\n7. Technology Tools\n- Augmented/virtual reality experiences\n- Interactive touchscreen displays\n- Digital catalog systems\n- Online collaboration platforms\n\n8. Emphasis on Digital Citizenship\n- Online safety education\n- Critical thinking skills\n- Responsible technology use\n- Information evaluation strategies\n\nThese trends suggest libraries becoming dynamic, technology-enhanced learning environments.",
